@page "/cards"
<PageTitle>Cards Example</PageTitle>

<h1 id="card-components">Card Components</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                Cards are the primary content container in Saascade documentation.
                Use the framework filter above to see framework-specific examples.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                Each design system renders a <code>&lt;Card&gt;</code> component with its own CSS class
                mapping. The content and structure remain the same across frameworks — only the
                class names differ.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="bootstrap-card">Bootstrap 5 Card</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                In Bootstrap 5, the <code>Card</code> component maps to the <code>.card</code> class
                with <code>.card-body</code> for inner content.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>// Bootstrap 5 setup
builder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;IDesignSystem&gt;(DesignSystems.Bootstrap5.VanillaBootstrap5);

// Razor usage
&lt;Card&gt;
    &lt;CardTitle&gt;My Title&lt;/CardTitle&gt;
    &lt;CardBody&gt;Content here.&lt;/CardBody&gt;
&lt;/Card&gt;</code></pre>

            <p>Renders as: <code>&lt;div class="card"&gt;&lt;div class="card-body"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="daisyui-card">DaisyUI Card</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                In DaisyUI, the <code>Card</code> component maps to the <code>.card</code> class with
                specializations like <code>bg-base-100</code>, <code>w-96</code>, <code>shadow-sm</code>.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>// DaisyUI setup
builder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;IDesignSystem&gt;(DesignSystems.Tailwind.DaisyUI);

// Razor usage
&lt;Card&gt;
    &lt;CardTitle&gt;My Title&lt;/CardTitle&gt;
    &lt;CardBody&gt;Content here.&lt;/CardBody&gt;
&lt;/Card&gt;</code></pre>

            <p>Renders as: <code>&lt;div class="card bg-base-100 w-96 shadow-sm"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;</code></p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="basecoat-card">Basecoat Card</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                In Basecoat, the <code>Card</code> component uses Tailwind utility classes to
                achieve a clean, minimal card style.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>// Basecoat setup
builder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;IDesignSystem&gt;(DesignSystems.Tailwind.Basecoat);

// Razor usage
&lt;Card&gt;
    &lt;CardTitle&gt;My Title&lt;/CardTitle&gt;
    &lt;CardBody&gt;Content here.&lt;/CardBody&gt;
&lt;/Card&gt;</code></pre>

            <p>Renders with Basecoat's minimal utility-first class composition.</p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("card-components", "Card Components"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("bootstrap-card", "Bootstrap 5 Card", 2),
    new TocItem("daisyui-card", "DaisyUI Card", 2),
    new TocItem("basecoat-card", "Basecoat Card", 2)
])" />

</div>
